>  [network]
isolate = "false"
default_network_options = ["isolate=false"]

These containers.conf option do not exist so that cannot work.

Yes right now this is hard coded as isolate is what docker always does, while in theory we could allow callers to explicitly set so that we do not override it the problem is we do the inverse on inspect and there it would be impossible to know if it was added explicitly or not so it would always remove the option confusing compose 


```
// Make sure to clone the map as we have access to the map stored in
// the network backend and will overwrite it which is not good.
options := maps.Clone(network.Options)
// bridge always has isolate set in the compat API but we should not return it to not confuse callers
// https://github.com/containers/podman/issues/15580
delete(options, nettypes.IsolateOption)
```
